{
  "texts": [
    "Its effectiveness is significant; studies demonstrate that, compared to baseline prompting strategies, it can increase the generation rate of correct test cases by up to 5 times and improve code coverage by over 100% [30,118].",
    "Dynamic Analysis.While static analysis provides a structural model of the code, dynamic analysis offers runtime information regarding its execution behavior, which is then provided as feedback to the LLM.",
    "The most direct application is coverage feedback.",
    "Frameworks such as CoverUp [9] execute a coverage tool to identify uncovered lines or branches.",
    "Precise information regarding these coverage gaps is subsequently fed into a new prompt, explicitly instructing the model to generate test cases targeting these specific gaps."
  ]
}